overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, comparing its current implementation against a detailed Statement
  of Work and questionnaire specification. Following the review, the user
  proceeded to implement several key missing features. This included integrating
  a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with critical safety warnings
  for high scores. Additionally, the application was enhanced to detect and
  report on Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome, providing tailored recommendations for each. Finally, a dedicated
  "Resources & Next Steps" section was added to both the web and PDF versions of
  the report, featuring placeholder links to external sleep and mental health
  resources. The implementation involved modifications across data types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic.
